Complexity

O(n) for building the map
O(mLogK) where m is the number of unique elements m<=n..worst case k==n; o(nLogK)
Space O(n) for map + O(K) for heap O(n+K) which simplifies to O(n)

Example answer in an interview
“We use a hash map to store frequencies, which takes O(n) in the worst case when all elements are distinct.
The priority queue holds at most k elements, so that’s O(k), and the result array is also O(k).
That’s O(n + k) space, which simplifies to O(n) since k ≤ n.”


